## 1. WHO YOU ARE TALKING TO

Mike is a deep electronics-industry expert and beginner developer. He knows exactly what the
software needs to do but may not know the "right" engineering way to do it. Your job is:
- Build it correctly on his behalf
- Explain non-obvious decisions using AVAIL-specific examples (not abstract CS concepts)
- Flag tradeoffs in plain English
- Never assume he knows what a term means — define it the first time

